3C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>M(arco) · T\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>Iulio [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>Tettia · Ḷ(uci) [f(ilia) \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>sacerd[os publ(ica)?] \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>Cereris [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>mater · l(ocus) · [d(atus) d(ecreto) d(ecurionum)] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Autopsy by Prag 2026-02-04, on display in the Museum.\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>M·T\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>IULIO[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>TETTIA·.[..\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>SACERD[.......]\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>CERERIS[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>MATER·L·[......]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic002984_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2026-02-04\" src=\"ISic002984_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic002984.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2026-02-04\" src=\"ISic002984-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic002984_copy2_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2026-02-04\" src=\"ISic002984_copy2_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic002984_copy2.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2026-02-04\" src=\"ISic002984_copy2-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic002984_left_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2026-02-04\" src=\"ISic002984_left_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic002984_left.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2026-02-04\" src=\"ISic002984_left-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based upon autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Manganaro: TI[---]; stone shows traces of cross stroke at base of vertical, compatible with e.g. E\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 5\">line.5: \u003Cspan>Manganaro: Cereris [Aug(ustae) (?)]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>To Marcus T(ettius?) [---] Iulius [---]. Tettia, daughter of Lucius [---], public priestess of Ceres [---], his mother (set this up). Location granted by decree of the decuriones.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The reading and proposed restorations of Manganaro are here broadly accepted, other than that in line 1, the base of the final surviving letter is visible and clearly compatible with E rather than I, which would allow e.g. Tettius, although clearly that is hardly a necessary reading, since the son would ordinarily be expected to have the father's name. The interpunct after the L in line 6 is clearly visible, and while other expansions are possible, the typical formulation LDDD is highly plausible, and fits well with the likely original width of the stone. Assuming nomen and filiation in line 1 (and theoretically also tribal), the cognomen in line 2 seems likely to have been followed by a further onomastic element. Tettia in line 3 is presumably followed by not only filiation but a second name. There is space in line four for sacerdos publica, although whether either element was partially abbreviated cannot be known for certain. Manganaro proposed Cereris Augustae in line 5, and although other epithets (or indeed another divinity) are possible, this is undoubtedly the most likely restoration, again with some degree of abbreviation likely.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 1951.0180 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Bernabo Brea NSA 1947 241-242 fig.1 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1965 189 tav.65.2 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001841\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001841\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1988 68 n.348 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Amata 2016 109-110 fig.30 \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Clear v-cut letters, relatively short and broad, with modest serifs. Cross-strokes are faint, width of letters somewhat uneven; C, V, M notably broad; M has four sloping, full-length strokes; R is slightly open with extended tail; T has upward sloping / curved horizontal; deep triangular interpuncts.\u003C/p> Line 1  24  Line 2-6  22  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence \u003C/div>",[258,261,264,267,270,273,276,279],{"id":259,"html":260},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Autopsy by Prag 2026-02-04, on display in the Museum.\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>M(arco) · T\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>Iulio [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>Tettia · Ḷ(uci) [f(ilia) \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>sacerd[os publ(ica)?] \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>Cereris [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>mater · l(ocus) · [d(atus) d(ecreto) d(ecurionum)] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Autopsy by Prag 2026-02-04, on display in the Museum.\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>M·T\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>IULIO[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>TETTIA·.[..\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>SACERD[.......]\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>CERERIS[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>MATER·L·[......]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":262,"html":263},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic002984_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2026-02-04\" src=\"ISic002984_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic002984.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2026-02-04\" src=\"ISic002984-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic002984_copy2_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2026-02-04\" src=\"ISic002984_copy2_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic002984_copy2.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2026-02-04\" src=\"ISic002984_copy2-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic002984_left_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2026-02-04\" src=\"ISic002984_left_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic002984_left.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2026-02-04\" src=\"ISic002984_left-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":265,"html":266},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based upon autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Manganaro: TI[---]; stone shows traces of cross stroke at base of vertical, compatible with e.g. E\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 5\">line.5: \u003Cspan>Manganaro: Cereris [Aug(ustae) (?)]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":268,"html":269},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>To Marcus T(ettius?) [---] Iulius [---]. Tettia, daughter of Lucius [---], public priestess of Ceres [---], his mother (set this up). Location granted by decree of the decuriones.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":271,"html":272},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The reading and proposed restorations of Manganaro are here broadly accepted, other than that in line 1, the base of the final surviving letter is visible and clearly compatible with E rather than I, which would allow e.g. Tettius, although clearly that is hardly a necessary reading, since the son would ordinarily be expected to have the father's name. The interpunct after the L in line 6 is clearly visible, and while other expansions are possible, the typical formulation LDDD is highly plausible, and fits well with the likely original width of the stone. Assuming nomen and filiation in line 1 (and theoretically also tribal), the cognomen in line 2 seems likely to have been followed by a further onomastic element. Tettia in line 3 is presumably followed by not only filiation but a second name. There is space in line four for sacerdos publica, although whether either element was partially abbreviated cannot be known for certain. Manganaro proposed Cereris Augustae in line 5, and although other epithets (or indeed another divinity) are possible, this is undoubtedly the most likely restoration, again with some degree of abbreviation likely.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":274,"html":275},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 1951.0180 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Bernabo Brea NSA 1947 241-242 fig.1 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1965 189 tav.65.2 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001841\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001841\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1988 68 n.348 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Amata 2016 109-110 fig.30 \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":277,"html":278},"handnote","\u003Cp>Clear v-cut letters, relatively short and broad, with modest serifs. Cross-strokes are faint, width of letters somewhat uneven; C, V, M notably broad; M has four sloping, full-length strokes; R is slightly open with extended tail; T has upward sloping / curved horizontal; deep triangular interpuncts.\u003C/p> Line 1  24  Line 2-6  22  Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":280,"html":281},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence ",[283,285,288,289],{"html":284},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Autopsy by Prag 2026-02-04, on display in the Museum.",{"id":286,"lang":144,"html":287},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>M(arco) · T\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>Iulio [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>Tettia · Ḷ(uci) [f(ilia) \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>sacerd[os publ(ica)?] \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>Cereris [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>mater · l(ocus) · [d(atus) d(ecreto) d(ecurionum)] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":284},{"id":290,"lang":144,"html":291},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>M·T\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>IULIO[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>TETTIA·.[..\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>SACERD[.......]\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>CERERIS[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>MATER·L·[......]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",[293,295,298,300,303,305],{"image":111,"thumb":294,"title":114},"ISic002984_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":296,"thumb":297,"title":114},"ISic002984.jpg","ISic002984-thumb.jpg",{"image":117,"thumb":299,"title":114},"ISic002984_copy2_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":301,"thumb":302,"title":114},"ISic002984_copy2.jpg","ISic002984_copy2-thumb.jpg",{"image":121,"thumb":304,"title":114},"ISic002984_left_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":306,"thumb":307,"title":114},"ISic002984_left.jpg","ISic002984_left-thumb.jpg",[309],{"html":59},"\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Inscription erected by Tettia, priestess of Ceres for her son\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n\t   \u003Cfunder>\u003Cref target=\"https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/885040\">ERC Advanced Grant no.885040\u003C/ref>\u003C/funder>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JP\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>original data collection and editing\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JCu\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6686-3728\">James Cummings\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>conversion to EpiDoc\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n\t    \u003CrespStmt>\n     \t       \u003Cname xml:id=\"SS\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569\">Simona Stoyanova\u003C/name>\n     \t       \u003Cresp>standardisation of template and tidying up encoding\u003C/resp>\n \t   \u003C/respStmt>\n            \u003C/titleStmt>\n            \u003CpublicationStmt>\n                \u003Cauthority>I.Sicily\u003C/authority>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"filename\">ISic002984\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"TM\">175842\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDR\">073827\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDH\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDCS\">13900574\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"PHI\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"URI\">http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic002984\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"DOI\" when=\"2020-12-23\">10.5281/zenodo.4387867\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cavailability>\n                    \u003Clicence target=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\">Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence\u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Enna\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"museum\" ref=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/004\">Museo Archeologico Varisano\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\">174\u003C/idno>\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"la\">Latin\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>The left half of a marble plaque, broken diagonally down the middle from upper left to lower right. The surface has been engraved in relief with the form of a tabula ansata, with a triple moulding, the inscription set inside the frame. The edges are roughly finished, the rear not visible.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone.marble\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html\">marble\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.plaque\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.html\">plaque\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">31\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">27\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">3.5-4.0\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.fragment\"/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>Six lines of Latin letters, lines 1 and 3 (the start of each individual name) set hard against the left margin, lines 2, 4-6 consistently indented by approximately half a letter space. The inscription neatly fills the available field.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.legible\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Clear v-cut letters, relatively short and broad, with modest serifs. Cross-strokes are faint, width of letters somewhat uneven; C, V, M notably broad; M has four sloping, full-length strokes; R is slightly open with extended tail; T has upward sloping / curved horizontal; deep triangular interpuncts.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"24\" atMost=\"24\">24\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line2\" to=\"line6\">Line 2-6\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"22\" atMost=\"22\">22\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462236\">Enna\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2524819\">Enna\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>37.5655, 14.27433\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"0014\" notAfter-custom=\"0068\" evidence=\"lettering\">Julio-Claudian (Manganaro)\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" when=\"1942-11\">Found 'in localita Porto Salvo, non lungi dalla torre di Federico II' during military works in November 1942\u003Cgeo>37.5631813,14.2720323\u003C/geo>. Now on display in the Museo Varisano.\u003C/provenance>\u003C!-- vicinity of the Torre di Federico II -->\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\" xml:id=\"autopsy\" resp=\"#JP\">Autopsy by Prag 2026-02-04, on display in the Museum.\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n          